Privacy Policy for SmartClock
Effective Date: 1/1/2026
Owner: Pixlnauts
Contact: pixelcryptonauts@gmail.com

Pixlnauts ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how SmartClock ("the App") handles your data.

1. Data Collection and Storage
Local Storage:
-User-entered data (reminders, notes, todos, alarms, calendar events, conversations, core memory, wallet data) is stored locally on your device only.
-We do not access, collect, or transmit this data to our servers.

Google Drive Backup (Optional):
-You can manually back up your data to your personal Google Drive account using the backup feature in the App.
-We do not have access to your Google Drive. All data is stored in your own Google account under your control.
-Wallet seed phrases are encrypted before backup for additional security.
-Backups are manual and only occur when you initiate them.

4. External Links
SmartClock may contain links to third-party websites (e.g., GitHub, Terms of Service, blockchain explorers). We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these external sites.

5. No Tracking or Analytics
-We do not collect location data, analytics data, usage statistics, or any other personal information.
-We do not use cookies, trackers, or advertising networks.

6. No Payments
SmartClock does not process payments. If users choose to donate, they are redirected to external platforms. We do not handle or store payment information.

7. Children's Privacy
SmartClock is intended for general audiences and does not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13 years old. If you believe a child has provided data to SmartClock, please contact us immediately.

8. Data Security
-All sensitive data (wallet seed phrases) is encrypted using industry-standard encryption before being stored locally or backed up to Google Drive.
-However, you are responsible for securing your device and Google account. Use strong passwords and enable two-factor authentication.

9. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted here with a new "Effective Date." Continued use of SmartClock after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

10. Contact Us
For questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at pixelcryptonauts@gmail.com.
